(24, 'Harissa', 'images/harissa.jpg', 'Take in the stunning views and rich history of Harissa, a hilltop sanctuary overlooking the Mediterranean!', '$75.00', '$90.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d13233.909674475226!2d35.64261314182734!3d33.98026897094166!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x151f40ca8b5ed947%3A0x8791c18842a56812!2sHarissa!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683044236914!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Harissa is a small town located in the hills overlooking the Bay of Jounieh in Lebanon. It is a popular destination for both locals and tourists alike, thanks to its stunning views, historical attractions, and vibrant culture.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the main attractions in Harissa is the iconic statue of Our Lady of Lebanon, a towering 15-ton bronze statue of the Virgin Mary that overlooks the town and the bay below. Visitors can take a cable car up to the statue and explore the surrounding area, which includes a church, a museum, and a variety of souvenir shops and restaurants.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn addition to the statue of Our Lady of Lebanon, Harissa is also known for its stunning views of the bay and the surrounding mountains. Visitors can take scenic hikes through the hills, visit local wineries and vineyards, or simply relax and take in the beauty of the area.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFor those interested in history and culture, Harissa also offers a number of fascinating attractions. The town is home to a number of churches and monasteries, including the Monastery of St. Paul and the Monastery of St. Anthony, both of which date back to the 17th century. Visitors can also explore the nearby town of Jounieh, which is known for its lively nightlife, shopping, and dining scenes.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Harissa is a unique and charming destination that offers a combination of natural beauty, historical attractions, and vibrant culture. Whether you\'re exploring the iconic statue of Our Lady of Lebanon, taking in the stunning views of the bay, or experiencing the local history and culture, a trip to Harissa is sure to be a memorable and enriching experience.', 8),
(25, 'Great Wall Of China', 'images/img-8.jpg', 'Experience The Grandeur Of The Great Wall Of China And Take In The Stunning Scenery.', '$90.00', '$120.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3036.958774346302!2d116.5677999752556!3d40.43191175471643!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x35f121d7687f2ccf%3A0xd040259b950522df!2sGreat%20Wall%20of%20China!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v16829', 'The Great Wall of China is one of the world\'s most iconic landmarks and a must-see destination for anyone traveling to China. The wall is a series of fortifications that were constructed along the northern borders of China over many centuries, with the earliest sections dating back as far as the 7th century BC.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Great Wall stretches for over 13,000 miles and consists of many different sections, each with its own unique features and attractions. Some of the most popular sections for visitors include the Badaling section, which is the most well-preserved and easily accessible section of the wall, and the Mutianyu section, which is known for its stunning views and challenging hiking trails.\r\n<br><br>\r\nVisitors to the Great Wall can take in breathtaking views of the surrounding countryside and explore the many watchtowers, guardhouses, and other fortifications that were built along the wall. The wall is also home to a number of historical and cultural attractions, including ancient temples, monuments, and museums that offer insights into the history and culture of China.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn addition to exploring the Great Wall itself, visitors can also experience the many other attractions and activities that the region has to offer. These include visiting the nearby Forbidden City and Tiananmen Square in Beijing, taking a boat ride on the nearby Ming Tombs reservoir, and trying local delicacies such as Peking duck and dumplings.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, the Great Wall of China is a must-see destination for anyone interested in history, culture, and natural beauty. Whether you\'re exploring the wall itself, taking in the stunning views of the surrounding countryside, or experiencing the local culture and cuisine, a trip to the Great Wall is sure to be an unforgettable experience.', 9),
(26, 'Shanghai', 'images/shanghai.jpg', 'Discover the modern marvels and rich cultural heritage of Shanghai, China\'s bustling metropolis!', '$85.00', '$95.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1747234.747009073!2d119.10779880329717!3d31.204993132894526!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x35b27040b1f53c33%3A0x295129423c364a1!2sShanghai%2C%20China!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1682975501', 'Shanghai is a vibrant and dynamic city located on the east coast of China. Known for its modern skyscrapers, historic landmarks, and thriving cultural scene, Shanghai offers something for everyone.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the most popular attractions in Shanghai is the Bund, a historic waterfront area located along the Huangpu River. Here, visitors can take in stunning views of the city\'s iconic skyline, explore the many shops and restaurants, and stroll along the waterfront promenade.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAnother must-see attraction in Shanghai is the Shanghai Tower, one of the tallest buildings in the world. Visitors can take a high-speed elevator to the top of the tower and enjoy panoramic views of the city from the observation deck.\r\n<br><br>\r\nShanghai is also known for its vibrant art and cultural scene. Visitors can explore the many museums and galleries throughout the city, including the Shanghai Museum, which features a vast collection of Chinese art and artifacts. The city is also home to a thriving theater and music scene, with performances ranging from traditional Chinese opera to contemporary rock concerts.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFood lovers will also find plenty to enjoy in Shanghai, with a diverse array of local and international cuisine available throughout the city. Some popular local dishes include xiaolongbao (steamed soup dumplings) and shengjianbao (pan-fried pork buns).\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Shanghai is a dynamic and exciting city that offers a wealth of attractions and experiences for visitors. Whether you\'re exploring the historic landmarks, taking in the stunning views from the Shanghai Tower, or experiencing the local art and culture, a trip to Shanghai is sure to be an unforgettable experience.', 9),
(27, 'Lhasa', 'images/lhasa.jpg', 'Explore the mystical beauty and rich culture of Lhasa, China, on a journey of a lifetime!', '$75.00', '$90.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d221902.4291189307!2d90.99302107826496!3d29.65523141451362!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x376133ca20bbf821%3A0x5851567ed41b17a4!2sLhasa%2C%20Tibet%2C%20China!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683008499299!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Lhasa, the capital city of Tibet, is a spiritual and cultural hub that attracts visitors from around the world. Located high in the Himalayan Mountains, Lhasa is home to a number of historic and religious landmarks, as well as stunning natural beauty.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the most popular attractions in Lhasa is the Potala Palace, a towering fortress that was once the residence of the Dalai Lama. The palace features a stunning array of murals, sculptures, and other religious artifacts, and offers breathtaking views of the city below.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAnother must-see attraction in Lhasa is the Jokhang Temple, one of the holiest sites in Tibetan Buddhism. The temple features a stunning collection of religious art and artifacts, and is a popular destination for pilgrims and tourists alike.\r\n<br><br>\r\nVisitors to Lhasa can also explore the many markets and bazaars throughout the city, which offer a wide variety of Tibetan handicrafts, textiles, and other goods. The Barkhor Street market, located in the heart of the old city, is particularly popular and offers a unique glimpse into Tibetan culture and daily life.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFor those interested in outdoor activities, Lhasa also offers plenty of opportunities for hiking, trekking, and other adventures. The nearby Namtso Lake, one of the highest lakes in the world, is a popular destination for nature lovers and offers stunning views of the surrounding mountains and landscapes.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Lhasa is a unique and fascinating destination that offers a wealth of cultural, spiritual, and natural attractions. Whether you\'re exploring the historic landmarks, shopping for Tibetan handicrafts, or taking in the breathtaking views of the Himalayas, a trip to Lhasa is sure to be an unforgettable experience.', 9),
(28, 'Burj Khalifa', 'images/img-9.jpg', 'Get ready to reach new heights at Burj Khalifa, the world\'s tallest building and an iconic symbol of Dubai\'s modern architecture and engineering feats!', '$160.00', '$190.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3610.1786555706963!2d55.269762970857606!3d25.197196928449934!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3e5f43348a67e24b%3A0xff45e502e1ceb7e2!2sBurj%20Khalifa!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683009704234!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Burj Khalifa, located in Dubai, is the tallest building in the world and a must-visit attraction for anyone visiting the city. Standing at 828 meters tall, the Burj Khalifa is an engineering marvel that offers stunning views of the city and the surrounding landscape.\r\n<br><br>\r\nVisitors can take an elevator ride to the observation deck on the 124th floor, known as At the Top, where they can enjoy panoramic views of Dubai and beyond. The observation deck features interactive exhibits that provide information about the building\'s construction and the city\'s history.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFor those looking for an even more luxurious experience, the Burj Khalifa also features the world\'s highest restaurant, At.mosphere, located on the 122nd floor. Visitors can enjoy a gourmet meal while taking in the breathtaking views of the city.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn addition to its observation deck and restaurant, the Burj Khalifa is also home to residential apartments, offices, and a luxury hotel. The building\'s unique design and impressive height make it a popular subject for photographers, and the nightly light show that illuminates the building is a must-see for anyone visiting Dubai.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, a visit to the Burj Khalifa is a once-in-a-lifetime experience that offers unparalleled views of Dubai and the surrounding landscape. Whether you\'re looking to dine in the world\'s highest restaurant, take in the stunning views from the observation deck, or simply marvel at the engineering feat that is the Burj Khalifa, a visit to this iconic building is sure to be unforgettable.', 10),
(29, 'Dubai Miracle Garden', 'images/dubaimiraclegarden.jpg', 'Escape to a breathtaking oasis at Dubai Miracle Garden, featuring over 45 million flowers in stunning displays and intricate designs that will leave you in awe!', '$100.00', '$110.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3595.1486468882194!2d32.63647597421424!3d25.69950197739101!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x144915c41edadf61%3A0x7693895c346c7d81!2sLuxor%20Temple!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683009814609!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Dubai Miracle Garden is a stunning floral paradise located in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. It is one of the world\'s largest flower gardens and is home to over 45 million flowers, including a variety of colorful blooms, sculptures, and structures.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe garden is spread over an area of 72,000 square meters and features a variety of themed gardens, including the heart-shaped flower beds, the Emirates A380 floral structure, and the world\'s largest flower arrangement in the shape of a Disney character. The garden also features a butterfly garden, a floral clock, and a 3D flower display.\r\n<br><br>\r\nVisitors can enjoy a leisurely walk through the gardens, taking in the beautiful sights and scents of the various flowers. There are also plenty of photo opportunities throughout the garden, with several areas set up specifically for taking pictures.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Dubai Miracle Garden is open from November to May, when the weather is cooler and more conducive to enjoying the outdoor garden. There are also several cafes and food stalls located throughout the garden, providing visitors with a variety of dining options.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, the Dubai Miracle Garden is a must-see attraction for anyone visiting Dubai who appreciates natural beauty and stunning floral displays. The garden is a true testament to human creativity and imagination and offers a unique experience that is both relaxing and awe-inspiring.', 10),
(30, 'Yas Island', 'images/yasisland.jpg', 'Experience paradise on Yas Island: a stunning blend of luxurious resorts, thrilling theme parks, and pristine beaches.', '$90.00', '$100.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d58095.81985430544!2d54.56177824107479!3d24.485846962643482!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3e5e457d9c174315%3A0xbea25f33cf37e48e!2sYas%20Island!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683009774505!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Yas Island is a man-made island located in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates, and is one of the country\'s top tourist destinations. The island features a wide range of entertainment and leisure options, including world-class theme parks, luxury hotels, shopping malls, restaurants, and more.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the island\'s biggest attractions is Ferrari World Abu Dhabi, a massive indoor theme park that is dedicated to the legendary Italian sports car brand. The park features a variety of thrilling rides and attractions, including the world\'s fastest roller coaster, the Formula Rossa, which reaches speeds of up to 240 km/h.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAnother major attraction on Yas Island is the Yas Waterworld, an outdoor water park that features over 40 rides, slides, and attractions, including the world\'s first hydro-magnetic tornado water slide. Visitors can also relax on the island\'s beaches, go shopping at the Yas Mall, or enjoy a round of golf at the Yas Links Abu Dhabi.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFor those looking for a luxurious stay, Yas Island features several high-end hotels, including the Yas Viceroy Abu Dhabi, which is built over the Yas Marina Circuit Formula 1 race track and features stunning views of the track and the surrounding area.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Yas Island is a great destination for anyone looking for a fun and exciting vacation in Abu Dhabi. With its world-class theme parks, luxurious hotels, and stunning natural beauty, the island has something to offer for visitors of all ages and interests.', 10),
(31, 'Machu Picchu', 'images/img-11.jpg', 'Embark On An Unforgettable Journey Along The Inca Trail In Peru, And Discover The Magic Of Machu Picchu.', '$90.00', '$100.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3883.9838385620574!2d-72.49989642619838!3d-13.226330787112936!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x916d9a5f89555555%3A0x3a10370ea4a01a27!2sMachu%20Picchu!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683009918113!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Machu Picchu is a world-famous ancient Incan city located high in the Andes Mountains of Peru. The city was built in the 15th century and abandoned just 100 years later, but its unique architecture and stunning setting have made it one of the most popular tourist destinations in the world.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe city is located on a ridge overlooking the Urubamba River valley and is surrounded by towering mountains and lush forests. Its buildings were constructed from polished stone blocks that were carefully cut to fit together without the use of mortar. The city\'s most famous structures include the Temple of the Sun, the Intihuatana stone, and the Room of the Three Windows.\r\n<br><br>\r\nVisitors can reach Machu Picchu by hiking the Inca Trail, which takes several days and offers stunning views of the surrounding mountains and valleys. Alternatively, visitors can take a train to the nearby town of Aguas Calientes and then hike or take a bus up to the site.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOnce at Machu Picchu, visitors can explore the ruins on their own or hire a guide to learn more about the history and significance of the site. There are also several hiking trails in the area that offer stunning views of the surrounding mountains and valleys.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Machu Picchu is a must-see destination for anyone visiting Peru or South America. Its stunning natural setting, unique architecture, and rich history make it one of the most fascinating and awe-inspiring sites in the world.', 11),
(32, 'Huacachina', 'images/huacachina.jpg', 'Enjoy the serene oasis views in the heart of the Peruvian desert with a tour of Huacachina!', '$80.00', '$105.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3869.8251021050487!2d-75.76568357617813!3d-14.087499636340283!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x9110e3010800b101%3A0x136be001d08a4223!2sHuacachina%2011000%2C%20Peru!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683009961634!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Huacachina is a small desert oasis located in southwestern Peru, just a few miles from the city of Ica. The oasis is surrounded by towering sand dunes and is a popular destination for adventure-seekers and tourists looking to experience the beauty of the Peruvian desert.\r\n<br><br>\r\nLegend has it that Huacachina was created when a beautiful Incan princess was bathing in a nearby river and was surprised by a hunter. As she fled, the water that covered her body turned into the oasis that we see today. Nowadays, Huacachina is a popular tourist destination and attracts visitors from all over the world.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the main attractions in Huacachina is sandboarding, which involves riding down the towering sand dunes on a board. Visitors can also take a dune buggy tour of the area or go on a camel ride through the desert. There are also several restaurants and bars in the area where visitors can relax and enjoy the stunning desert views.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn addition to its outdoor activities, Huacachina also has a rich history and culture. Visitors can explore the nearby city of Ica and learn about the region\'s history and visit local museums, such as the Regional Museum of Ica. They can also visit the local vineyards and try the famous Peruvian pisco, a type of brandy that is made from fermented grapes.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Huacachina is a unique and beautiful destination that offers a mix of outdoor adventure, culture, and history. Whether you\'re looking to sandboard down towering dunes or explore the local vineyards, Huacachina is a must-see destination for anyone visiting Peru.', 11),
(33, 'Arequipa', 'images/arequipa.jpg', 'Explore the colonial beauty and cultural richness of Arequipa, Peru, on an unforgettable journey of discovery!', '$75.00', '$90.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d61238.541868151435!2d-71.58021158168084!3d-16.404048336943237!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x91424a487785b9b3%3A0xa3c4a612b9942036!2sArequipa%2C%20Peru!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683010002554!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Arequipa is a beautiful city located in southern Peru, known for its colonial architecture, stunning natural scenery, and rich cultural heritage. The city is surrounded by three volcanoes, including Misti, Chachani, and Pichu Pichu, which offer breathtaking views of the Andes Mountains.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the main attractions in Arequipa is the historic center, which was declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2000. The center features colonial-era buildings, such as the Santa Catalina Monastery, which was founded in the 16th century and is considered one of the most beautiful religious buildings in South America. Other notable landmarks include the Plaza de Armas, the Cathedral of Arequipa, and the Compañia de Jesus Church.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn addition to its historic attractions, Arequipa is also known for its cuisine, which is a mix of Spanish, indigenous, and African influences. Visitors can try local dishes, such as rocoto relleno, a spicy stuffed pepper dish, and chupe de camarones, a hearty shrimp soup. The city is also famous for its picanterías, traditional restaurants that serve local dishes and drinks.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOutside of the city, visitors can explore the nearby Colca Canyon, one of the deepest canyons in the world, which is home to the Andean condor and other unique wildlife. They can also visit the Salinas and Aguada Blanca National Reserve, a protected area that features a diverse range of flora and fauna.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Arequipa is a fascinating destination that offers a mix of history, culture, and natural beauty. Whether you\'re exploring the city\'s historic center, trying local cuisine, or venturing out into the surrounding countryside, Arequipa is a must-see destination for anyone visiting Peru.', 11),
(34, 'Santorini', 'images/santorini.jpg', 'Escape to the enchanting island of Santorini, Greece, where the breathtaking views create a truly magical and unforgettable experience!', '$120.00', '$150.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d12842.15957277748!2d25.421870694070446!3d36.42032580772081!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x1499cdce05e3bce9%3A0x9f4c192bbefa1db!2sThera%20847%2000%2C%20Greece!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683010059109!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Santorini is a picturesque island located in the Aegean Sea, in the Cyclades archipelago of Greece. Known for its whitewashed buildings, stunning views of the Mediterranean, and beautiful beaches, Santorini is a popular destination for travelers from around the world.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe island is famous for its unique architecture, which features traditional white-washed buildings with blue roofs and doors. Visitors can explore the charming towns of Oia, Fira, and Imerovigli, which offer breathtaking views of the Mediterranean Sea and the island\'s rugged coastline.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the top attractions in Santorini is the caldera, a massive volcanic crater that was formed by a volcanic eruption over 3,000 years ago. Visitors can take a boat tour of the caldera or hike the trail that winds around its edge, which offers stunning views of the island\'s unique landscape.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSantorini is also known for its beautiful beaches, including the black sand beaches of Perissa and Kamari and the red sand beach of Akrotiri. Visitors can swim, sunbathe, or enjoy water sports like windsurfing, kayaking, and stand-up paddleboarding.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFinally, Santorini is a popular destination for food and wine enthusiasts, offering a wide range of traditional Greek dishes, fresh seafood, and local wines. Visitors can sample local specialties like fava, a traditional yellow split pea puree, and tomatokeftedes, tomato fritters that are a Santorini specialty.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Santorini is a must-visit destination for anyone looking to experience the beauty and culture of Greece. Whether you\'re exploring the island\'s charming towns, relaxing on its beautiful beaches, or indulging in its delicious cuisine, Santorini is sure to be a highlight of your trip to Greece.', 12),
(35, 'Mykonos', 'images/mykonos.jpg', 'Discover the Mediterranean charm and allure of Mykonos, Greece, where sun-kissed beaches, charming streets, and endless fun await!', '$110.00', '$135.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d101356.61373613021!2d25.298445662579258!3d37.451414045144276!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x14a2b8b4f03c9b91%3A0x78d164471e79b4a1!2sMykonos!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683010104605!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Mykonos is a beautiful island located in the Aegean Sea, in the Cyclades archipelago of Greece. Known for its vibrant nightlife, stunning beaches, and charming white-washed buildings, Mykonos is a popular destination for travelers from around the world.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the top attractions in Mykonos is its beautiful beaches, which are famous for their crystal clear waters and stunning natural scenery. Some of the most popular beaches on the island include Paradise Beach, Super Paradise Beach, and Psarou Beach, all of which offer a range of water sports and activities for visitors to enjoy.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMykonos is also known for its charming white-washed buildings, which can be found in the island\'s main town, Chora. Visitors can explore the narrow streets of Chora, which are lined with shops, restaurants, and cafes, or visit the island\'s famous windmills, which date back to the 16th century.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAnother highlight of Mykonos is its vibrant nightlife, which includes a range of bars, clubs, and restaurants that stay open until the early hours of the morning. Some of the most popular spots on the island include the Scandinavian Bar, the Tropicana Beach Bar, and the Cavo Paradiso club, which has hosted some of the biggest names in electronic music.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFinally, Mykonos is a popular destination for food and wine enthusiasts, offering a wide range of traditional Greek dishes, fresh seafood, and local wines. Visitors can sample local specialties like louza, a cured meat made from pork, and kopanisti, a spicy cheese spread that is a Mykonos specialty.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Mykonos is a must-visit destination for anyone looking to experience the beauty, culture, and nightlife of Greece. Whether you\'re relaxing on its beautiful beaches, exploring its charming towns, or enjoying its vibrant nightlife, Mykonos is sure to be a highlight of your trip to Greece.', 12),
(36, 'Meteora', 'images/meteora.jpg', 'Experience the wonder and spiritual serenity of Meteora, where towering rock formations and stunning vistas transport you to a world of peace and tranquility!', '$90.00', '$110.00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3068.7987902908876!2d21.62801467496594!3d39.721704371559795!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x13590faee8327f39%3A0x7127add4d8bc32ff!2sMeteora!5e0!3m2!1sen!2slb!4v1683010144092!5m2!1sen!2slb', 'Meteora is a unique destination located in central Greece, known for its stunning landscape of towering rock formations and ancient monasteries perched on top of them. The word \"meteora\" means \"suspended in the air\" in Greek, and it\'s easy to see why when you visit this incredible site.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Meteora rocks were formed millions of years ago by a combination of natural geological processes, and they are now home to six active monasteries that date back to the 14th and 15th centuries. These monasteries were built by hermit monks who sought solitude and isolation, and they can only be reached by climbing steep steps or using a system of ropes and pulleys.\r\n<br><br>\r\nToday, Meteora is a popular tourist destination that attracts visitors from around the world. Visitors can explore the monasteries, which are filled with ancient religious artifacts and stunning frescoes, and enjoy panoramic views of the surrounding landscape from their vantage points high above the ground.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn addition to the monasteries, Meteora is also a popular destination for rock climbing and hiking, with a network of trails and routes that wind their way through the stunning landscape. Visitors can also explore the nearby town of Kalambaka, which is home to a number of traditional Greek tavernas and restaurants serving local specialties like moussaka and pastitsio.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOverall, Meteora is a must-visit destination for anyone interested in history, religion, or natural beauty. Its stunning landscape and ancient monasteries offer a unique glimpse into the history and culture of Greece, and its network of hiking trails and climbing routes provide ample opportunities for adventure and exploration.', 12);

